  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7110.61 sitting right near the max negative gamma strike at 7115 (-3814.5M), dealers are likely buying the dip aggressively as they're short gamma at this level, creating amplified buying pressure. The massive positive gamma wall at 7200 (+8025.7M) should act as strong resistance where dealers will sell rallies, while the PIN regime suggests mean reversion back toward the 7150-7200 zone where gamma is most supportive. Key levels to watch are 7115 (max negative gamma turning point) and 7200 (major resistance wall).\n\n**Bottom line:** expect a bounce from current levels with upside capped near 7200.",
